HKUST Alumni Wine Association (HKUSTAWA) was founded by a group of wine enthusiasts in October 2016.  Our vision is to promote wine culture and responsible drinking among alumni and current students*.   

Since our inauguration, we have connected 300+ alumni over glasses of wines through our workshops and gatherings.  Different styles of events have brought our members and friends fun time, thus created a HKUST's wine community for wine knowledge exchange or simply enjoyment with wine buddies.  

We strive to bring members more benefits, from discounts on wines & spirits purchases, special offers at restaurants & bars, to promotional offers on wine events in town.  The more wines you taste, the more you learn. 

* Students must be over 18 years old in order to join our events or register as member.

---

Our Vision

The objectives of the HKUST Alumni Wine Association (HKUSTAWA) are:
1. to engage and connect alumni through wine appreciation activities;
2. to promote wine appreciation culture among alumni and students;
3. to promote the advancement of wine knowledge for work or for leisure;
4. to promote responsible drinking;
5. to collaborate with organizations and entities that support our mission.
